<br>
 First lets start with raids. Back in Kunark and Velious, most mobs could be killed in less then the time it took defensive to wear out, AoW and Vulak being the main exeptions, thus making Defensive tanks the core of any guild. Thus every serious guild recruited and worked up their tanks in HP to do the task at hand. Warriors at this time were very happy, thus never took the time to question how good or bad their class was. <br>
<br>
Enter Shadows of Luclin, this is where Verant, using the Vulak styled AC, decided they could tone down melee and improve casters. While Melee soon learned to love the 1,12,1, 1, 12, 12, 1, 48, 1, 1 ,1 , 12, 1  type mobs the casters were able to hit the mobs for normal damage. Now the lower damage wasn't just a nerf to melee in general, but more of a nerf to tanks that use Defensive. Defensive is good for 3 minutes, with SoL mobs taking well over 3 minutes and in some cases 30  minutes to kill, defensive has no real impact other then to buy time for the CH chain to get going. Once a CH chain is going any high HP tank with good mitigation could tank any mob in the game.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now lets talk about agro. Agro is the only thing a warrior with tons of HP is worried about. Having 7700  hp means nothing if you cant keep the mob on ya. Taunt button works for @#%$, this is the cruel fact. I think Verant only made a taunt button to give us something to push, thinking that its doing some good, when in truth does next to nothing, might as well press Sense Heading. So, Verant decides that warrior need better agro, thus come up with weapon procs called Enraging Blow to help hold agro. Only problem on Enraging Blow that is 80%   of the warrior population will never see one of these weapons as uber guilds sweep them up or block others from having to prevent competition on other mobs. Now the only other thing that can grab agro is AE Taunt. Feking Useful Skill! Sad fact is it can only be used once every 15 minutes so, its a one shot &quot; Gimmick &quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry for the history lesson, now on to the meat of the matter. So we are all happy with warriors? They do so so damage, AC past 1200 means next to nothing, and our beloved HP are now only a few hundred HP from the next plate wearing class, and sadly the only thing that defines a warrior is the level 55 skill Defensive ( though I do like Evasive in many cases over Def ). Now how would you feel if you are no longer wanted? Yes, a class that could become extinct and replaced in guilds! I am sure many are LOL right now but let me go into some detail on this.<br>
<br>
Warrior in Top End Gear ( self buffed only ):<br>
<br>
HP: 6200ish<br>
AC: 1800ish<br>
<br>
DPS: Roughly 80 DPS<br>
<br>
Top Skills: Defensive, Evasive, Aggressive, Furious, AE Taunt<br>
<br>
<br>
This is pretty much what a warrior brings to a group / raid / solo.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Paladin in Top End Gear ( Self Buffed ):<br>
<br>
HP: 5711 ( 6711 )<br>
AC: 2095 ( 2127 )<br>
<br>
<br>
DPS 1H: Roughly 40 DPS<br>
<br>
<br>
Skills:<br>
<br>
CH Lay of Hands<br>
Shield of Words<br>
Resolution<br>
Greater Remove Curse<br>
Stuns<br>
Divine Stun<br>
90% Res<br>
Roots<br>
Divine Aura<br>
Group Heals<br>
Self Regen<br>
Self Haste<br>
Symbol of Naltron<br>
BMB<br>
Heals<br>
Slay Undead ( Damage that can hit 6k on a hit )<br>
Dispells<br>
Cures<br>
Anti Undead Spells<br>
Holy Forge<br>
<br>
<br>
Here is the kicker though, Paladins can hold agro better then a warrior and in the case they lose agro can get it back better then any class other then a SK. When it comes to Combat Agility, Natural Durability, Combat Stability they get an extra class skill that takes them higher in all 3 abilities.<br>
<br>
As a puller they hands down beat a Warrior. Divine Aura for things that DT ( since DT is now 20k Damage based ), stuns on pulls or Root, LoH on the run if hp is low.<br>
<br>
Holding Agro is a breeze to with all the stuns and weapon procs they can add to a weapon. No need to wait for a proc, just cast it when needed or let the proc work it.<br>
<br>
Damage: 1H the Warrior easily wins with duel attack and duel wield, but goto 2H and the Paladin is toe to toe with the Warrior and surpasses the warrior vs undead mobs.<br>
<br>
Groups will more then likely take in Paladins, because they can hold the agro, they come with an arsenal of useful skills that benefits the party, can heal and stop runners. Also CH is very efficient on 7k  Paladin.<br>
<br>
Raids will now open up more to a Paladin to MT then ever before. As 400 to 500 hp separating the top MT hp from the top Paladin hp the difference is noticable but small. Paladins can easily make this up in agro department and in versatility when not in the MT line up.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
One last thing to note, there is a new shield rules being tested on test server. The shield allow for more damage mitigation. While it would a huge change for a warrior to go to a shield and lose a Enraging Blow Weapon ( loss of agro ), Paladins and SKs will feel right at home and now obtaining better mitigation then a warrior, while not suffering a loss of agro.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now my only hopes are that Verrant takes a real look at where they placed the Warrior and where he stands in the 3 environments ( Group, Raid, Solo ). Though hearing that thread from Rich Waters that warriors in PoP only need a few &quot; Gimmiks &quot; left me depressed to say the least. I will continue to play my warrior as its a class I worked hard at and still love to play. Just that it saddens me that Verrant has no foresight to see what their so called &quot; Balancing &quot; has done. At least they did a good job on the Wizard with their AA skills and spells, its good to see a pure class remain undisputed champion of their half-breed classes.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
