There is also the diffuculty curve. When breaking *new* ground, for the most part your gunna need warrior to tank it, however, after that, farmed it a little, farmed similar mobs for so long that its boosted the pal/sk HP/AC gear enuff so its possible for them to tank it, there almost no matter what HAS to be a point, (except at the very upper crux of melee damage) that through the aciqustion of gear, and AA points that a pal/sk can tank it, if not, because, a warrior of less gear, has to beable to tank it. The problem is, that due to mudflation, and the length of the time the game has gone on, is that the end of the curve is much easier to reach now.  If a pal/sk cannot ever tank a raid type mob except at the very upper crux of pure melee damage (AoW type DPS) there would be a trickledown that makes a worse tank, to such a degree, that it is not good to have them be the main tank to in XP group, and as much as some warriors may like that, our utility/dps is *rarely* enuff to warrant our presence in an xp group.<br>
<br>
However, maybe suprisingly I do agree that warriors need some upgrades, I got some ideas, probably wont like em cause they came from a paladin, and I'll admit I&quot;m not as in touch with the issues, as a warrior is, but sometimes a outside perspective is good (just as a non warrior/pal/sk would beable to look at war/Knight balance with less of a biased eye, I'll admit it, i'm somewhat biased;P) <br>
<br>
So Here some ideas I had which I think might improve the warrior class, w/o breaking the game.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Taunt</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
On every taunt, the taunter gains Taunt skill/4 (Rough number) amount of hate, if they do not have agro of the mob. In addition, the way taunt currently works stacks with this, IE, on a sucessfull taunt, the taunter would get aggro + Skill/4. However, once they gain aggro, taunt works in the exact same way, IE, no taunt is added after agro is gained, with the exception of going from Non agro, to agro status.<br>
<br>
This would hopefully address being less reliant on procs, and beable to gain aggro more effectivly, however, to keep the game challenging, no taunt is gained, by the use of the taunt skill, after agro is established, so people still have to manage their aggro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Taunt Weapons</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
There is a lack of weapons between EB/SoD (If Sod is still aviable) besides the ever so hard to find Willsapper, besides the still rare, Skybreaker. These weapons would be added to the game<br>
<br>
On Gozzrems Lootable.<br>
<br>
Scimatar of Demolition<br>
Lore Magic Nodrop<br>
14/21<br>
10 AC 50 hp 5 sta 5 dex 10 SVM<br>
Effect: Demolition;1 Second Stun, 100 dmg<br>
<br>
On Chardok Queens Lootable<br>
Argent Sword of Striking<br>
Lore Magic<br>
13/22<br>
40 HP 5 ac 5 sta 8 SVD/p<br>
Effect: Argent Strike, 20 AC Debuff, 50 DD,<br>
<br>
These Two weapons would could give Warriors some more choice in weapons, and make the curve to EB Weapons more smooth.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> HP</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Since I doubt verant will ever nerf a class, espcially their beloved monks.<br>
Just as Clerics gain an innate 5% to all heals, Warriors would gain an innate 5% to all HP items.<br>
<br>
PE Would Be War/Pal/SK, all current BRD/RNG with the ability would be given their 5 points back. (i'm dreamin)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> AA</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Ambidex in addition to its current properties, would give offhand damage bonus, Lvl 1: 3, Lvl2, 6, Lvl 3, 9. (These numbers are for what it would be at lvl 60).<br>
<br>
Add Class AA for warriors: Weapons Training Mastery, 9 Points, Increases your attack while wielding any weapon by 75 points.<br>
<br>
Add Class AA for warriors: Skill Mastery (Need better name) This would raise all skill defensive skill caps, not already maxxed by 10 points.<br>
<br>
This would hopefully try to keep the proper ratios of dmg more in line at the end game.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Misc</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Warriors are hearty individuals, however, they dont deal with magic too well, Instead of Innate bonus resitance MR, change it to the CR/FR/DR/PR, as warriors are good in suriving in the elements. Due to their stanima, and surivibility, warriors have an innate 5% chance to outright resist ANY FR/CR/DR/PR attack<br>
<br>
Due to their lack of casting spells, and their general lack of knowledge about Magic, warriors take an extra 10% dmg from any spell marked magic, if the spell isnt outright resisted. (If it is resited, they take 0 damage)<br>
^ This is to balance out some of the other change to warriors, as to try to give the class a little bit more indiviudaulity.<br>
